    "body": "@karalabe Running tests is precisely the reason I'm running geth in dev mode actually. Only that I am unable to use the default chainId `1337`. I don't have any need for the networking, it's just that `networkId` is the only parameter in the command line that looked relevant. As I understand it, setting a custom genesis would be undoing a bunch of parameters that `dev` mode provides. \r\n\r\nPut simply, I'm just looking for a way to use a different chainId with dev mode. ",
